<br>
Every time something is said by a character of this class, it is transmitted to one of the following channels at random:  /ooc, /shout, /auction, /gu<br>
<br>
Gets innate crits when attacking with a fishing pole.<br>
<br>
Specialized line of disciplines:<br>
<br>
- Level 30:  /disc chickenout - Instantly transfer all aggro to a random character in the vicinity, and 10-second enhanced run speed.<br>
<br>
- Level 40: /disc darntheluck - Automatic /q issued upon reaching low health. <br>
<br>
- Level 50: /disc buggeroff - Instant gate to a random location where there is absolutely no chance of taking damage or being killed.<br>
<br>
- Level 60:  So little chance of ever reaching this level, that no discipline is necessary.<br>
<br>
Special alternate advancement system by which points are awarded based upon chat references made to Diablo, Britney Spears, or Star Wars Galaxies.<br>
<br>
New spell:  Imbue With Spellcasting Ability -- Allows characters of this class to get ports, rezzes, or Spirit of Wolf from warriors. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarthis>Sarthis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 2:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: d00d</span><hr size=1> I thought this up like a year ago when the same came up on Monkly Business.<br>
<br>
Dragoon.  Pure Melee class.<br>
<br>
No dual weild.  Double attack at level 1, like monks.  Plate Armor, but low avoidance.<br>
<br>
Most of their weapons would be 2hp weapons, like lances, but they'd have the option to use a shield and a 1h spear.  They'd be exclusively using spears though.<br>
<br>
Weapons for them would be extremely high ratio, since most of their damage is generated by high damage strikes, albiet not very fast ones.  They'd be equal in DPS to monks.<br>
<br>
Some kind of special attack at level 20 that did damage based off the ratio of their lance.  Animation would be a twisting thrust of some kind.<br>
<br>
Starting at level 10 and on up to level 65, they'd occasionally gain skills that could be used to attatch an additional proc onto their weapons, with varying properties.<br>
<br>
Allowable races would be, half elf, human, high elf, dark elf, iksar.  Essentially all the medium races except Vah Shir, because they suck. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><br>
